&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Accredited Clinical Coder Band 4 with 15% Recruitment &amp; Retention Premium&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;PLEASE NOTE WE ARE ONLY ACCEPTING APPLICATIONS FROM ACC CLINICAL CODERS&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Here at Sandwell and West Birmingham Hospitals NHS Trust we believe that everyone matters.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an Accredited Clinical Coder who is self-motivated and enthusiastic with excellent communication skills to join our team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will need to have significant coding experience and sound knowledge in the use of patient information and coding systems used within the NHS and can deliver a high standard of coding completeness and accuracy in a timely manner to meet commissioning and Payment by Results timescales. In return we offer ongoing training and development supporting all of our staff to develop professionally and personally.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will need to;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have experience of clinical coding a wide range of specialties.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrate a high level of accuracy, adhering to national standards and conventions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible in your approach you must be able to work as part of a team to tight deadlines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exhibit excellent analytical skills with a good knowledge of medical terminology, anatomy and physiology&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Sally Nicholds&lt;br /&gt;Job title: Clinical Coding Manager&lt;br /&gt;Email address: Sally.Nicholds@nhs.net&lt;br /&gt;Telephone number: 0121 507 6161&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Matthew Maguire, telephone 07971155721, email matthew.maguire@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
